One law I would nominate as almost constitutional is:

Every transformation must preserve or improve three quantities whenever possible:

1. Truthfulness (faithfulness to evidence and uncertainty)
2. Agency (the human is more capable afterward)
3. Coherence (the system remains internally and externally consistent)

That gives Pantheon something analogous to conservation laws in physics. New operators can be added indefinitely, but they should all be evaluated against the same invariant criteria. I think that moves the project closer to becoming a coherent cognitive architecture rather than just a growing collection of clever ideas.